    "SUMMARY": "Radim Řezník (born 20 January 1989) is a Czech footballer. He last played for FC Viktoria Plzeň. He has three caps for the Czech Republic national football team.\nŘezník started his league career at FC Baník Ostrava, where he played until 2011, when he moved to FC Viktoria Plzeň. Having represented various Czech youth teams, on 4 September 2014, Řezník debuted for the senior squad in a friendly match against the United States."
